content: Its a good version of the actual card game
Addictive. Enjoy the levels and trying to be the best
Would've been 5 stars if it had local multiplayer at least. Great game otherwise.
As much as I love this game, anyone who's ever played it knows it is hardly playable with fewer than 5 players. So until you add a couple of more AI's this game gets 3 stars.

Good game overall. If you have the screen orientation locked it ignores that, which is a small negative. The big issue is that multiplayer only works as pass and play. With this in my family library, I was hoping my husband and I could play against each other, but pass and play is too much. That being said, very simple game with a lot of Strategy still. Goes quick so you can play a few rounds at a sitting. Overall happy with the game. True multiplayer and it would be top 10.
Excellent port. Good when I have to wait for a short period of time.
Faithful replication of the game.

Bought for multi player. Why is it local only? Why doesn't the information page mention that? The entire point of an app version of a card game is so that you can play the game with people not in the same place as you. Very silly of the developers and disappointing.
Nice game... But please add online PVP patch... Would be great to be able to play against others players around the World.
Works and looks very good. Rounds go quick and sound and graphics are good. Gameplay is easy once you play 2 or 3 games. Reminds me a little like gin rummy. You have to plan ahead to win. Fun game.
Great digital version of 6 nimmit. Highly recommend
Great game. But can you add the option to lock orientation. I just can't play it when laying in bed. Keep rotating all the way. Really annoying P/s: I did turn off auto-rotate
replyContent: Sorry for that! Android 9 should support turning off Auto-rotate for the device. If this does not work: please contact us at support@application-systems.de and we can look for solutions to the issue.

content: This is now our favorite game to play as a couple while we are waiting for one thing or another. The only downside is that it is pass an play. (NOTE TO DEVELOPERS: we would pay a bit more for a bluetooth version) Great game play. Liked the game so much we bought the card version... our kids liked it so much, they ordered the card version. And the computer opponents are quite skilled. Play smart!
Good

a good game spoiled by poor ui. the bull icon on the card background makes 
numbers unreadable. needs a clear card-face option and needs to utilise 
screen real-estate more optimally.
Great game, but... unfortunately the fact that only the tops of my hand of cards is visible, the game is unplayable on my 7" tablet
replyContent: Sorry for the trouble you've experienced. Can you please get in touch with support@application-systems.co.uk so that we can try to find out what goes wrong on your specific device. The app runs fine on 10s of thousands tablets so we should be able to make it run on yours.

content: Nice adaptation of the classic card game.

The game is fun to play. However after install this app, sometime all apps in the recent list doesn't show up. I have to restart my phone to fix this but it will occure again. After remove the app, I doesn't have recent app list problem again, so it should be this app that cause it.
Cool
Verizon Ellipsis hand cards are cut off.  Cannot see far left \ far right card numbers
Good game, but has an annoying bug where pressing putting the phone to sleep will prevent any current game being resumed
Attractively presented, well worth a couple of bucks.
It reminds me tons of fun with friends.
I like the game . it's funny and easy to play but not easy to win. User interface is clear.

This is a great game and the interface is smooth. But the fact that it doesn't support advanced variant (cards on left) means i will not play it. It also doesn't support a 6 player game, which is considered the best setup. Regret buying it due to these shortcomings.
Excellent game. It appears simple, but the more time you spend with it the more you will develop your game strategy.
Ok for the odd short blast, soon gets boring.
Addictive,  very well made. No issues. Would be nice to have online multi player though.
Needs no explanation if you have played the card game - great for all ages and at least your brain is stimulated unlike all the 'freemium' games. Highly recommended!

Great simulation of the addictive card game on which me & my friends have spent countless hours. Pros:Excellent concept, exciting & funny graphics, multiplayer support on the same device, concise and thorough help for the newcomers,challenging AI. Cons: kinda repetitive music, 3d rendering of game board makes the game unnecessarily taxing for your android device. Expect some lagging and framerate loss unless you are running on a high-end tablet. Also, there should be an option to turn off card animation

A very well done implementation of 6 Nimmt!  Easy AI is not easy to beat. Loads of play value here. Perhaps could use more multiplayer support.
Fixed.
replyContent: Please contact support@application-systems.de and let us know the name of your device and the version of Android you are running, so that we can look into that problem. We definitely didn't see that on the devices we used, but of course there are a lot of them out there and we really want to fix this.

content: Starting the app is slightly problematic:  my MotoX (Android 4.4.3) takes more than a minute to acknowledge any input on the first splash screen each time the app starts.  (The Nexus 7 2013 is much faster.)  But once things get going, the app is responsive and clear; the game plays well; it's quite amusing.  I wonder at the (coincidence?) increased battery use from mdnsd when playing the game, but it's not large enough to be problematic.
